From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jami Daemon <jami@jami.net>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] storage: guard against null bucket in Storage::expire

StorageBucket::erase() was dereferenced through the per-value
store_bucket pointer without checking it for null. Values that are
stored without an associated storage bucket (store_bucket left at its
default nullptr) leave that pointer null, so when they expire the
periodic maintenance call reaches StorageBucket::erase with a null
"this" pointer and crashes while reading a member
(NULL_CLASS_PTR_READ / c0000005).

Skip the bucket bookkeeping when no bucket is attached to the expiring
value. The value itself is still removed from the store as before.
---
 include/opendht/storage.h | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/opendht/storage.h b/include/opendht/storage.h
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/include/opendht/storage.h
+++ b/include/opendht/storage.h
@@ -395,7 +395,8 @@ Storage::expire(const InfoHash& id, time_point now)
         if (v.expiration <= now) {
             del_num++;
             size_diff -= v.data->size();
-            v.store_bucket->erase(id, *v.data, v.data->size());
+            if (v.store_bucket)
+                v.store_bucket->erase(id, *v.data, v.data->size());
             it = values.erase(it);
         } else
             ++it;
-- 
2.40.1
